race.comment: LONGER ROUTE (1) doesn't win out of turn but was excellent here last week, sticking on strongly into a close third. He backs up quickly, draws kindly for Milnes, and the rise in trip looks ideal. MELLIFLUENT (2) comes through the same race and was a touch plain there, but his prior form reads well for this level. Toeroek taking over is a strong lead and he can bounce back. MORTHAN EFFICIENT (4) warmed to the task late when resuming at Geelong 12 days ago. He'll be fitter and the extra ground suits. THERMODYNAMIC (5) maps to push forward from the low draw and should be right there when they quicken. Not one to underestimate. TOP OF THE RIDGE (3) will appreciate a more genuine tempo and be saved for the final shot at them. Capable of grabbing a slice.
